scene.message:
Igor: Welcome{nl}
to the Velvet Room...{waitkey}{clearbox}This room awakens the{nl}
ancient forms that dwell{nl}
in the human heart.{waitkey}{clearbox}Won't you show me{nl}
your Persona?{waitkey}{ret}

Igor: Well then,{nl}
what shall we discuss?{waitkey}{nl}
{ctl0e:23}{ret}

Igor: When you wish for a{nl}
new Persona, I shall fuse{nl}
one and make it for you.{waitkey}{clearbox}To make a Persona, I must{nl}
fuse demons summoned{nl}
from the demon realm.{waitkey}{clearbox}But to summon a demon,{nl}
a certain card is needed.{waitkey}{clearbox}On that card is written{nl}
the spell to call{nl}
forth a demon.{waitkey}{clearbox}We call it a Summon Spell{nl}
Card, and each demon{nl}
holds but one.{waitkey}{clearbox}And so, to fuse you must{nl}
first gather Spell Cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}You must negotiate with{nl}
demons and obtain the{nl}
cards yourselves.{waitkey}{clearbox}When you meet a demon,{nl}
fighting isn't everything.{waitkey}{clearbox}Do you understand?{waitkey}{clearbox}They do not always{nl}
wish to fight...{waitkey}{ret}

Igor: To wield a newly{nl}
fused Persona as your{nl}
own power...{waitkey}{clearbox}fusing alone is not enough.{waitkey}{clearbox}Only by incarnating the{nl}
Persona into your body{nl}
can you master its power.{waitkey}{clearbox}You may incarnate up to{nl}
three Personas in one{nl}
person.{waitkey}{clearbox}A newly fused Persona{nl}
I keep in safe care.{waitkey}{clearbox}When you have need,{nl}
call on me to incarnate.{waitkey}{clearbox}I can hold up to sixteen{nl}
Personas, so swap them{nl}
as the need arises.{waitkey}{clearbox}Personas, like human{nl}
natures, are myriad - each{nl}
differs in form and heart.{waitkey}{clearbox}Discern them, and use each{nl}
as the moment demands.{waitkey}{clearbox}Master them so, and you'll{nl}
become a fine Persona{nl}
user indeed.{waitkey}{ret}

Igor: You may incarnate{nl}
up to three Personas{nl}
per person.{waitkey}{clearbox}One of them is "active" -{nl}
ready to be summoned{nl}
during battle.{waitkey}{clearbox}To summon is to call your{nl}
Persona forth in combat.{waitkey}{clearbox}The other two remain{nl}
in a charged state.{waitkey}{clearbox}In battle, a Persona Change{nl}
can make one of them{nl}
active.{waitkey}{clearbox}An active Persona bolsters{nl}
your many abilities.{waitkey}{clearbox}Without a Persona's power,{nl}
you are no different{nl}
from ordinary humans.{waitkey}{clearbox}You'd have no strength to{nl}
endure a demon's magic.{waitkey}{clearbox}Take one head-on, and{nl}
you'd likely not survive{nl}
at all.{waitkey}{clearbox}But incarnate a Persona,{nl}
and your defense against{nl}
magic rises sharply.{waitkey}{clearbox}Some find their strength{nl}
rises, others their luck.{waitkey}{clearbox}This too is a Persona's{nl}
power - though all of it{nl}
is a hidden side of you.{waitkey}{clearbox}Once incarnated, study{nl}
your own status well.{waitkey}{clearbox}You'll see just how{nl}
you have changed.{waitkey}{clearbox}At first, no one can draw{nl}
a Persona's full power.{waitkey}{clearbox}But the more you summon it,{nl}
the more of its ability{nl}
you draw forth.{waitkey}{clearbox}As your summoning skill{nl}
grows, more attacks open{nl}
up in battle.{waitkey}{clearbox}Yet even with stronger{nl}
attacks to choose, the SP{nl}
to summon stays the same.{waitkey}{clearbox}You grow through battle -{nl}
but never forget, your{nl}
Persona grows too...{waitkey}{ret}

Igor: This is merely{nl}
my meddling, but...{waitkey}{clearbox}A Persona grows in eight{nl}
stages, so now and then{nl}
try raising one to the end.{waitkey}{clearbox}Surely something good{nl}
will come of it...{waitkey}{clearbox}Also, fusion involves many{nl}
factors, from the subtle{nl}
to the great.{waitkey}{clearbox}For instance, even when{nl}
making the same Persona...{waitkey}{clearbox}which Spell Cards you{nl}
combined to begin with...{waitkey}{clearbox}the order of summoning...{waitkey}{clearbox}the affinity of the{nl}
demons' elements...{waitkey}{clearbox}the place of Terra and{nl}
Luna at fusion...{waitkey}{clearbox}whether you added some{nl}
other essence...{waitkey}{clearbox}I nearly forgot...{waitkey}{clearbox}During fusion, adding{nl}
items can bring about{nl}
changes as well.{waitkey}{clearbox}With some items the result{nl}
can be foreseen,{waitkey}{clearbox}but at times even I cannot{nl}
predict it - forgive me{nl}
when that happens.{waitkey}{clearbox}Still, it's worth a try...{waitkey}{clearbox}By the way, jewels can{nl}
change the class within{nl}
the same race of result.{waitkey}{clearbox}As for other items, I{nl}
recommend you try them{nl}
yourself.{waitkey}{ret}
